{
  "stem": "19210.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe that the funding for the soup kitchen, at least it began with the Jewish community of Lisbon.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Both the hospital and the soup kitchen were side by side and I believe it went back to the 1930s, at least, when the hostel was built.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as to how my Aunt Esther became involved, again, I'm assuming that she lived next door to Mr.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Torjman, who was one of the cooks in there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And also Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Torjman was in charge of the kosher meat distribution in Lisbon for the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His wife was my Hebrew teacher, personal tutor of Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so-- so they were friends and I'm assuming that because of Mr.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Torjman being at a soup kitchen, that he then somehow talked my Aunt Esther to work, as well, there and manage the soup kitchen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But primarily, it was built for the poor of the community.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I would say not just Jewish, there were other-- other members of-- that used to come by and no one was ever neglected a meal, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And later on, as the-- at the beginning of the war, Second World War and the Jewish refugees started to really coming to Lisbon, then they-- they divided two-- two halls and the largest hall became then the hall for the-- the dining room for the refugees.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It would probably seat within 120, 150 people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the other small dining room became the one used by the few Portuguese Jews, the poor of the community.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I used to go just to help my Aunt Esther.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had a great relationship and I loved to listen to all the different languages.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
